   "source": [
    "# 🤖 LLM API Integration — Text Intelligence Pipeline\n",
    "\n",
    "Portfolio project demonstrating integration of an LLM (Anthropic Claude) into a text-analysis pipeline (sentiment, topic extraction, feature generation).\n",
    "\n",
    "This is a cleaned version of the original notebook. Execution outputs and environment-specific traces have been removed so the notebook can be run reproducibly.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Structure & purpose\n",
    "- Input: customer reviews (e-commerce)\n",
    "- Tasks: sentiment classification, topic extraction, feature generation, data enrichment\n",
    "- Integration: calls to Anthropic Claude (configurable), with a simulated mode if no API key is provided.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "metadata": {},
   "execution_count": null,
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Create project folders (idempotent)\n",
    "import os\n",
    "os.makedirs('llm_api_integration/notebooks', exist_ok=True)\n",
    "os.makedirs('llm_api_integration/data', exist_ok=True)\n",
    "os.makedirs('llm_api_integration/outputs/plots', exist_ok=True)\n",
    "print('folders created: llm_api_integration/...')\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "metadata": {},
   "execution_count": null,
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Write a minimal config.yaml for the pipeline\n",
    "config_text = '''project:\n  name: \"LLM API Integration - Text Intelligence Pipeline\"\n  version: \"1.0.0\"\n  author: \"SAID\"\n\napi:\n  provider: \"anthropic\"\n  model: \"claude-sonnet-4-6\"\n  max_tokens: 512\n  temperature: 0.1\n\ndataset:\n  name: \"E-commerce Customer Reviews\"\n  n_samples: 50\n\noutput:\n  results_json: \"outputs/api_results.json\"\n  features_csv: \"outputs/llm_features.csv\"\n'''
    "with open('llm_api_integration/config.yaml','w',encoding='utf-8') as f:\n",
    "    f.write(config_text)\n",
    "print('wrote llm_api_integration/config.yaml')\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "metadata": {},
   "execution_count": null,
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# requirements (write file)\n",
    "requirements = [\n",
    "    'anthropic>=0.30.0',\n",
    "    'pandas>=2.0.0',\n",
    "    'numpy>=1.24.0',\n",
    "    'scikit-learn>=1.3.0',\n",
    "    'matplotlib>=3.7.0',\n",
    "    'seaborn>=0.12.0',\n",
    "    'pyyaml>=6.0',\n",
    "    'tqdm>=4.65.0',\n",
    "    'jupyter>=1.0.0',\n",
    "    'ipykernel>=6.0.0'\n",
    "]\n",
    "with open('llm_api_integration/requirements.txt','w',encoding='utf-8') as f:\n",
    "    f.write('\n'.join(requirements))\n",
    "print('wrote llm_api_integration/requirements.txt')\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## How to run\n",
    "1) Create a virtual environment and install dependencies:\n",
    "```
",
    "python -m venv .venv\n",
    "source .venv/bin/activate   # (or .\\venv\\Scripts\\activate on Windows)\n",
    "pip install -r llm_api_integration/requirements.txt\n",
    "```
",
    "2) Set API key if you want to call Anthropic:\n",
    "```
",
    "export ANTHROPIC_API_KEY='sk-ant-...'
",
    "```
",
    "3) Open and run notebook: llm_api_integration/notebooks/llm_api_integration.ipynb\n"
   ]
  },
